name: v0.2.14
body: This is a release that fixes the issues mentioned in https://github.com/maticnetwork/bor/issues/300 and https://github.com/nomiclabs/hardhat/issues/2162 that users have been facing after London Fork (EIP1559).

name: v0.2.13
body: This release contains the changes required to activate London Fork (EIP1559 and related EIPs) on Mainnet.

url: \nNote: This is a hardfork and requires an update in genesis.

name: RLP Encode baseFee in Block Header
assets.name: bor_0.2.13-beta2_checksums.txt
body:
This release contains RLP encoding of an additional field, `baseFee` in the block header. Geth had added this in the Clique consensus changes for EIP1559 but we had missed to add this in bor. The impact is mainly on downstream applications as the client libs might have a problem with the coinbase value.

Since there is a change in the block seal hash, this requires a hard fork at the Jaipur Block at block 22,770,000 for Mumbai Testnet.

Please note that this is applicable **only for Mumbai** Testnet. On Mainnet, when we rollout EIP1559, we will be setting the same number for both London and Jaipur blocks.

name: Bor update for Mainnet release
body: This release contains some bug fixes and also a hardfork, please refer the instructions in https://forum.polygon.technology/t/v0-2-12-beta3-upgrade-for-bor-mainnet-post-block-22156660/369 to upgrade.

name: Bor Update for Mumbai Testnet
body: This release contains some bug fixes that we are testing on Mumbai Testnet.

name: Fix for writing bor receipts to ancient db
body: This release fixes a bug that was introduced in the previous version where the bor receipts were being written as an array of arrays instead of the expected flattened array inside an array.

url: \nThere was **no impact** of this bug in our network since all the nodes use `--syncmode=full` and this bug only affects nodes running with `--syncmode=fast`.

name: Upstream Changes from Geth v1.10.10
body: In this release, we have included all changes that are part of geth v1.10.10: https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/releases/tag/v1.10.10\n\nPS: This tag has not been created from `master` but from another branch `geth-v1.10.10` as `master` contains few new features that are currently being tested.

name: Fixed Memory Leak, Added Network Flags for Mumbai and Mainnet
assets.name: bor_0.2.9_checksums.txt
body:
In this release, we have fixed the memory leak issue in bor, added network flags that can be used while invoking bor and few other minor changes. Major changes are listed below:

- Memory Leak Fixed: The root cause for the memory leak was identified and fixed in #201. We had already fixed the memory bloat issue that was causing few nodes to consume the entire memory within minutes of starting bor in https://github.com/maticnetwork/bor/releases/tag/v0.2.9-beta1
- Network Flags: You can now start bor using bor --bor-mainnet and bor --bor-mumbai flags to connect to mainnet and mumbai networks respectively. The defaults can be found here: https://github.com/maticnetwork/bor/blob/6c7a9e1c410992486ce610ed3836cec35ba546e6/cmd/geth/config.go#L342-L386 and any params that need to be overridden can be passed separately.

**Pre-requisites**

Please upgrade the go version to v1.16 or above before updating.

name: Hot Fix for Memory Bloat
body: Some of the bor nodes have been facing memory bloat resulting in the process getting killed by the OS. This is a hot fix for the issue.

url: \nWe are also working with the geth team to include the change in geth if this is the agreed long term fix or discuss and come up with the long term fix.

name: Latest Updates from Geth
body: The major change in the release is this revert PR from Geth: https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/pull/23466

name: Updates from Geth v1.10.8
body: This release implements the latest changes from upstream geth v1.10.8 ([https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/releases/tag/v1.10.8](https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/releases/tag/v1.10.8) - hotfix release to patch a vulnerability in the EVM _CVE-2021-39137_). Below is the exhaustive list of changes in this release:

url: \n- Implemented new rpc/ipc method: `GetTransactionReceiptsByBlock` returns the transaction receipts for a given block number or hash
\nPlease note that this release **does not** activate the London hard fork in bor.

name: Geth Update v1.10.3
body: Bor v0.2.6 is a maintenance release. Major changes are as follows:

url: \n- Added flag for disabling bor logs

name: Berlin Fork Upgrade
body: Updated to latest (upstream) geth v1.10.1 that includes berlin hardfork changes and other changes. More details from geth: https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/releases/tag/v1.10.1

url: \nBerlin fork blocks on different networks of Bor and their expected schedules are as follows:

name: Beleza By The Beach (v0.2.2)
body: Bor v0.2.2 is the release with upgraded Geth (v1.9.24) and a major feature regarding state-sync.

url: \nWe recommend everyone to upgrade to this release and rebuild with Go 1.15.5.
\n* Better code structuring for future Geth updates https://github.com/maticnetwork/bor/pull/95
\n* Introducing state sync logs using block receipt https://github.com/maticnetwork/bor/pull/90
